I love jewellery, and I try when I travel to bring some home to remind me of the good memories. I have a Heathergem necklace bought from the factory in Scotland in 2013 with my family that was a seconds piece. It was the same day we visited Colloden, it is a yellow, green and pink heart with a leather strap. It has a small nick at the back, which makes it so unique, and special. I wear it a lot. It also reminds me of my Scottish grandfather who passed away almost five years ago who I was really close to. When I returned to Scotland this year in February, I bought a heather gems ring close to the border, with a similar "stone" encased in Stirling silver.
